text:
Kerry Vincent (' Flynn; 1 June 1945 – 2 January 2021) was an Australian television personality and baker. She lived and worked in the United States. She was a judge on many Food Network shows. She was also the co-founder of the annual Oklahoma State Sugar Art Show. In 2013, she was a judge in "The Great Australian Bake Off". Vincent was born in Wyalkatchem, Western Australia.
Vincent died of an illness on 2 January 2021 in Tulsa, Oklahoma. She was 75.
